  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2776",
  "title": "Facet values starting with `-` are considered exclusions by default",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nbug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nWhen facet values displayed in a refinement list (or menu, hierarchical menu) are starting with a dash like temperature: -80C then clicking on those values will fail because it will be understood as a facet exclusion by the Algolia engine. \r\n\r\nExample: https://codesandbox.io/s/jpkzxoo20v\r\n\r\nClicking on any refinement won't change anything\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nClicking on refinements should refine. Values should be automatically escaped.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\n\r\nWe could automatically escape refinement values to \"\\-80C\", since doing a refinement list with excludes is not today a feature. And if it is a feature at some point then it will be explicit not based on the data.\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n\r\nLatest\r\n\r\n<!-- Delete any HTML comment and non relevant questions -->\r\n",
